article.headline: Austin Peay 68, SE Missouri 67
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Austin Peay beat Southeast Missouri 68-67 Saturday night in a game where the lead changed 11 times and the score was tied six times. It was the 259th win in head coach Dave Loos' 17 seasons with the Governors (9-6). That makes Loos Austin Peay's career win leader. Missouri (6-12) started out strong with an 8-0 run in the first four minutes, but Austin Peay came back to tie the game 10-10 at 13:30. After that it was back and forth with Missouri up by three at the half, 41-38. Missouri continued to lead in the second half until the governors tied the score 46-46 at 15:24. But Missouri was up again at 13:03 and didn't lose the advantage until a layup by Derek Wright put Austin Peay on top with just over 8 minutes to go. After more back and forth a 3-pointer by Landon Shipley with 2:35 remaining finally gave Austin Peay a lead it could hold onto. Todd Babington led the Governors with 17 points, including 4 shots from the 3-point range. The team also was helped by Drake Reed with 11 points. Shipley and Fernandez Lockett scored 10 each. Brandon Foust led Southeast Missouri with 15 points and 12 rebounds. David Johnson and Marcus Rhodes contributed 14 each.
